This note describes the transitional relief applied by the entity on first-time recognition of heritage assets under GRAP 103 / IPSAS 45.

## 1. Approach

Where it was not practicable to determine the historical cost or fair value of heritage items previously held but not recognised, the entity has applied the transitional relief permitted by GRAP 103 / IPSAS 45 and has either:

- recognised the items at deemed cost based on the best available evidence at the date of transition; or
- not recognised the items as assets in the statement of financial position and instead disclosed their existence in the heritage register.

