## 6. Plan for subsequent recognition

The entity will, at each reporting date and at least annually:

- review the population of heritage items not yet recognised;
- consider whether new valuation evidence has emerged that would enable reliable measurement;
- recognise additional heritage assets where the recognition criteria are met; and
- update this transitional disclosure until the heritage register is materially complete.

